54.6	Philosopher_king	Philosopher king	Philosopher kings are the rulers, or Guardians, of Plato's Utopian Kallipolis. If his ideal city-state is to ever come into being, "philosophers become kings…or those now called kings …genuinely and adequately philosophize" (The Republic, 5.473d).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/Plato-raphael.jpg/100px-Plato-raphael.jpg
